The article expresses gratitude to Emperor Akihito and Empress Michiko on behalf of the American people as the Heisei era comes to an end and a new generation prepares to take the throne in Japan. It recognizes the importance of the relationship between the United States and Japan, particularly during the Cold War era. The First Lady and President Trump were honored to be guests of Emperor Akihito in 2017 and express their commitment to continuing the partnership and cooperation with Japan in the new era.